neosnatch (0.7.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Distribution expansion:
    - Native packages now ship for Debian/Ubuntu (.deb amd64 + arm64),
      Red Hat-family (.rpm x86_64 + aarch64), and a static-musl tarball
      for Alpine/NixOS/generic (x86_64 + aarch64).
    - install.sh autodetects dpkg / rpm / tarball and host architecture.
    - SHA256SUMS file attached to every release.
    - Release workflow fans out across the matrix and gates on
      Cargo.toml-vs-tag version match.

 -- SGC <oneill@sgc.ai>  Wed, 29 Apr 2026 22:00:00 +0000

neosnatch (0.6.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Banner restructure:
    - Hostname rendered as a 5-row block-letter wordmark (replaces the
      chafa-image / unicorn-ASCII default logo); centered, with the
      "N E O S N A T C H" tag below.
    - Title bar drops the "neosnatch ·" prefix.
    - Top section keys justified to the same column as Resources/Storage.
    - Daemons list moved out of the top section into Security after sudoers.
    - Storage rows show per-mount LUKS / unencrypted status next to fs.
    - Resources reordered: cpu, gpu, load, memory, swap.
    - Resources & Storage bars share alignment.
    - Network section terminates with two harmonized port blocks
      (docker-ports and system-ports) that share scope/port/target columns;
      the old Security `ports` row is removed.
    - WAN-IP appears at the top of Network (default URL switched to
      http://ip.sgc.ai — the upstream is HTTP-only).
    - Packages line includes the package manager (apt/pacman/apk/rpm).
    - Per-session listing in `users` plus anomalous-IP red flag from a
      snapshot-maintained known-hosts set.
  * Helper service (snapshot generator):
    - Drops to dedicated `neosnatch` system user with only
      CAP_DAC_READ_SEARCH + CAP_SYS_PTRACE.
    - Hardening: PrivateTmp, ProtectSystem=strict, ProtectProc=ptraceable,
      RestrictAddressFamilies=AF_UNIX AF_NETLINK, IPAddressDeny=any,
      KeyringMode=private, UMask=0077, RestrictFileSystems=@common,
      tightened SystemCallFilter, MemoryDenyWriteExecute.
    - Captures listeners-with-process-names, docker network names, docker
      container port publishes, failed units, sudoers, system + user
      crontabs, known-login hosts (anomaly seed), and advisories.
    - postinst creates the system user and writes a SupplementaryGroups
      drop-in for whichever of {docker, crontab} groups exist on the host.
    - Snapshot schema bumped to v4 (advisories, docker_container_ports,
      sudoers, cron_jobs, known_login_hosts).
  * Performance:
    - Reads /var/log/wtmp by seek-from-end (~100µs vs 11.5ms).
    - Login path never forks `apt-get`; advisories are read-only from
      /var/lib/update-notifier/updates-available, populated by helper.
  * CLI: --ports and --cron flags dump full listings as plain tables.
  * Drops chafa from Recommends; --logo is a hidden no-op for backwards
    compat.

 -- SGC <oneill@sgc.ai>  Wed, 29 Apr 2026 17:55:00 +0000

neosnatch (0.2.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian packaging.
  * Section-based renderer with bar gauges, vertical port/docker layout.
  * Privileged snapshot subcommand with systemd timer unit.
  * Hardening: snapshot service runs with ProtectSystem=strict,
    NoNewPrivileges, PrivateTmp, restricted ReadWritePaths.

